{
  "stem": "3022.6",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Unfortunately, their numbers are dwindling.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "From 70-some charges, we have now about 50 left.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We support Jews in Israel and also needy survivors from our organizations in New York.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And this is all done by charitable endeavors, by fundraisings.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And besides that, we contribute to many other charitable organizations.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "We gave close to half a million dollars to Beit Halochem, which is an organization that takes care of Israeli disabled veterans.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So at our world gathering in Florida about seven years ago, we committed ourselves.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And we collected close to half a million dollars and we gave to this organization.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Because we felt-- they put a plaque in the name of Krakow Jewry-- we felt this was the best way to honor [SOBS] our loved ones.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "We felt that this was the best way to pass on the legacy of their values, of their ethical will, so to speak, the things that we're exposed to, that we cherish most.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Most of these values, really, I wasn't aware of them.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "As I told you, I took philosophy, and I took Nietzsche, Kant, and all the other philosophers.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I came away very cold, very disappointed.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I turned to the treasury of the Jewish people.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I started to study the things that I should have studied when I was young.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I started to appreciate the philosophy of our faith and the values that our faith teaches us.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And those were the values.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The people, even if they were not educated in Jewish law, in Jewish traditions, they knew.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I lived under three guidelines, the three words that guided of my life from my father-- [NON-ENGLISH], [NON-ENGLISH], [NON-GERMAN], which means, you are forbidden, it's not done, and it's not becoming a Jew.",
      "word_count": 33
    }
  ],
